<item>
            <title>[LU-4379] Unable to set max_pages_per_rpc at client mount time</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4379</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is very convenient to be able to set all Lustre client tuning parameters (max_pages_per_rpc, max_rpcs_in_flight, ...) right after having Lustre mounted.&lt;br/&gt;
Unfortunately, with Lustre 2.4 we are unable to set max_pages_per_rpc tunable for osc associated to an unavailable target. This is annoying as we do not necessarily know when the targets will become available.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will propose a patch to address this issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;br/&gt;
Sebastien.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
